procedure.description: This procedures creates a new FitNesse instance using CLI.

formalParameter.description: Directory where fitnesse.jar is located.
The directory in which FitNesse expects to find its page root. It defaults to the fitnesse.jar directory plus '/FitNesseRoot'.

The port number that FitNesse new instance listens to. The default is 80 because this is the port that internet browsers use by default. If your machine already has a web server running, it will be using port 80, so FitNesse should be set up to use a different port, like 8080.
Additional command line arguments to create a new Fitnesse instance. (For example, -o, -l <path> {no logging}, -Xmx...).
Path where java bin is located.
Timeout for the step execution in minutes. Blank means no timeout.

step.description: Set the timelimit for the next step
This procedures creates a new FitNesse instance using CLI parameter

procedure.description: This subprocedure allows users to run FitNesse tests and suites on an existing fitnesse instance.

formalParameter.description: Provide the hostname for the existing FitNesse server.

The port number that FitNesse new instance listens to. The default is 80 because this is the port that internet browsers use by default. If your machine already has a web server running, it will be using port 80, so FitNesse should be set up to use a different port, like 8080.
Provide the path and file name for the resulting xml file.
Checkbox to stop the existing instance.
The name of the FitNesse wiki page being referenced to execute as the test target. (For example, FitNesse.SuiteAcceptanceTests or FitNesse.SuiteAcceptanceTests.SuiteSlimTests.ChainTest)
Select the type for the target.
Timeout for the step execution in minutes. Blank means no timeout.
